---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const delivery = [
  ['Deep understanding guaranteed', 'Training and review flow built in. Your team reviews every model, every assumption, every line. Your least experienced consultant can explain the staging logic to a skeptical technical stakeholder.'],
  ['No branding in the output', 'The generated project belongs in your delivery workflow, not on a SNADLY invoice line.'],
  ['House style support', 'Naming conventions, folder structure, documentation format, macros, and test defaults align to how your team works.'],
  ['Standard artefacts', 'SQL and dbt output that another consultant or an internal team can pick up and extend.'],
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SNADLY for BI consultancies"
  description="Run more warehouse projects without hiring more engineers. Generated dbt in your house style, reviewed and owned by your team."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">For BI consultancies</p>
    <h1>Run more projects without hiring more engineers.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Your team already delivers great warehouse projects. SNADLY generates the
      repeatable build work in your house style so your people spend more time
      on the parts clients actually pay for — and walk into every meeting with
      real mastery of the models.
    </p>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="button" href="mailto:adrian.white@gmail.com">Talk to us</a>
      <a class="button button-secondary" href="#white-label">How it works</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-muted split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">The problem</p>
      <h2>You can only grow by hiring juniors. Juniors in front of clients is where things break.</h2>
      <p>
        Your senior engineers are the bottleneck. You hire juniors because it
        is the only way the numbers work. But a junior consultant who doesn't
        fully understand the staging layer is one client question away from a
        loss of confidence. You need every person on the project to be able to
        defend the work, not just the senior who built it.
      </p>
      <p>
        SNADLY generates the build base in standard dbt SQL, fully documented,
        so your consultants master the warehouse faster than if they'd written
        every line themselves.
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="note">
      <h3>Best fit</h3>
      <p>Consultancies that already deliver warehouse or BI projects and want to run more of them without compromising client confidence or delivery quality.</p>
      <h3>The client-facing story</h3>
      <p>Your team delivers architecture, metric definitions, business interpretation, and adoption. SNADLY handles the initial build base. The client never hears the name SNADLY — they see your people, your standards, your quality.</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">AI you can trust</p>
    <h2>Not another AI demo. Real dbt your team can inspect.</h2>
    <p>
      You have heard every AI pitch in the last two years. Most produce
      models that look right and break under scrutiny. Worse: a consultant
      in front of a client with generated code they cannot explain.
    </p>
    <p>
      SNADLY's output is standard dbt SQL. No AI at runtime. No black box.
      Every transformation is documented with assumptions, column
      descriptions, and lineage. Your team reviews every model before it
      reaches a client. The result: your people understand the warehouse
      more deeply than if they had built it from scratch.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-muted" id="white-label">
    <p class="eyebrow">White-label delivery</p>
    <h2>The output should look like your best work.</h2>
    <div class="item-grid">
      {delivery.map(([title, text]) => (
        <article>
          <h3>{title}</h3>
          <p>{text}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section cta">
    <p class="eyebrow">First step</p>
    <h2>Trial it on a recent project shape.</h2>
    <p>The right test: can SNADLY generate the staging layer and marts your team would have built for a recent client engagement — in your house style, with documentation your junior consultant can defend?</p>
    <a class="button" href="mailto:adrian.white@gmail.com">Talk to us</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
